2006", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC4556.html", target="_top", tooltip="This document describes protocol extensions (hereafter called PKINIT) to the Kerberos protocol specification.  These extensions provide a method for integrating public key cryptography into the initial authentication exchange, by using asymmetric-key signature and/or encryption algorithms in pre-authentication data fields. [STANDARDS-TRACK]"];
